content.detailedDescription: We had a birthday party on this date. my wife at about 11:43 pm took a trash bag to the trash can. while she was at the trash can a bright flash of light filtered through the trees. she stepped out onto the road and watched as this light flashed two more times as it traveled south down the road. she ran to the house to get me and my daughter, grandson. the four of us scanned the sky to the south from the yard.  nothing was observed so we went to the road. we scanned the sky from north, west to south. nothing was observed for several minutes. my grandson first noticed a strobe flash to the ssw at about one fourth of a mile coming over top of a small woods. i picked it up then and we both watched it come on a direct line at us. it moved fast and was low to the ground. probably not more that 150 feet from the ground. it would strobe, then it wouldn't strobe again for about a second and had moved a distance of maybe 100 yards. as it approached  us the strobe turned east before it got the end of the yard. my grandson lost sight of it then. i moved back into the yard and watched this strobe continue east for about one fourth of a mile where it cleared the top of another woods and disappeared.
content.summary: Brilliant white fast moving  intermitant strobe

content.detailedDescription: My wife went out to get the paper before work about 6:15 am. she came back in the house and wanted me to come outside and view an object flashing red and green. i observed this star like object at about 120-125 degrees on the compass and about 30-35 degrees inclination. this object appeared to be moving with the normal star field motion. i watched this object for about 15 minutes before i went back inside. this object continued to flash red and green. the object was smaller than jupiter in the sky, but had a more intense brilliance.
content.summary: Star like object flashing red and green

content.detailedDescription:
My son saw the objects first, there were at least three of them and possibly five.  they were stationary for the most part though one or two raced about the sky in movements that a plane could not do, ie. fast dips and sharp turns that would tear a plane apart.  they were at least a mile west of the park straight down interstate 20 toward alabama.  i would put the altitude at about 1000 to 1500 feet.  i pointed my canon gl2 and started shooting.  i did not have a tripod so some of the images are shaky, but you can clearly see three of the objects hovering in place in a triangular formation.  the ones that were moving were no longer visible.  i used the digital zoom to its maximum, and as the object wafted in and out of automatic focus you can see it pulsating.  one pulsed blue, the other red.  i did not shoot close-ups of the third.  an unusual aircraft (in terms of its large bright signal lights) can be seen flying in the airspace between the park and the object.  this same jet or another one identical to it came by several minutes later and did the exact same thing.  these were not stars or planets.  the north star was to the left as we faced the objects and was brightly lit.  there were few stars that could be seen over the corona of the amusement park, and none at that low orientation in the sky.  the objects all seemed to rotate vertically like a wheel.  i shot for several minutes, but since it was like shooting the points of pins in space, i couldn't get any better video so i stopped.  i work in the media and have hundreds of hours in choppers.  i am familiar with optical anomalies and tricks of light with cameras, and these images were not those.
this is actually the second ufo event i have witnessed, but it is the first where i actually had a camera.
i plan to post the video on youtube soon.
content.summary: My son and i saw the objects while at six flags amusement park

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were at  erwin park in mckinney.  she walks the dogs and i usually fly my model electric airplanes.  while watching my airplane i spoted a bright white light comming toward me from the south.  it stoped in a position just above and to the right of the cresent moon.  i called my wife to come watch.  she brought the dogs and sat in the grass right beside a bike trail.  i was distracted by bicyclest asking about my plane as i was flying it.  for some reason i got to thinking that it was just jupiter and when my plane landed went to put in a fresh battery for the next flight.  all the while my wife continued to watch the light.  she said that it seemed to move slightly side to side but stayed in the same spot.  she said that it would get very bright and then dim. after she watched it for about 10 min. she turned her head and when she turned back it was gone.  i found jupiter way east of the moon and could see venus in the west but i never again found the bright star like light again.  the altitude of this light was above the flight path of the jets aproaching dfw.  i have pictures of an earlier event with a bright white light that hovered over the park.
content.summary: Bright light moving toward me the stops and hovers for 10 min.

content.detailedDescription: Just left the casino in atlantic city, new jersey,,,went  on the boardwalk, looking out over the ocean, when one of the other people spotted it.There had to be over 50 people in our area that saw it ,,,very clearly,,,it appeared to be a classic saucer shape,,,,over the water,,,30 degrees or so ,,,about 2 miles out over the water,,traveling south...We all saw it, some folks had a camera,,,almost everyone took out their cell phones to call someone...It traveled what appeared to be 50 mph...In a straight line ,,,then suddenly it just went straight up and out of sight at a very fast speed....No lights,,,just a lead grey  color....I am certain that it should be in the new jersey or phila.Pa.  news by tomorrow..I left the shore about 4:30 pm,,,and arrived home about 6:00 pm.....I can only guess that it had to be over 100 feet long,,,some of us agreed to that size, some thought larger...I  am enclosing a photo,,,not the object that we saw...I picked this out of a ufo sight,, merely to give you some idea of its size and shape....I repeat...This photo is not the actual object that we all saw.....
content.summary: Standing on the boardwalk looking out over the atlantic ocean with about 40 other perple

content.detailedDescription: At around 11:00pm i was standing in a small park which is part of the motion picture library on lacienga blvd. i notice a mad standing alond on one side of the field kicking a soccer ball around but not really paying much attention to it. my dog started to chase various object around the park when i noticed what looked like 3 to 4 white headlights in the sky flying towards me. i assumed nothing and went about my business watching my dog. after a minute or two i looked back in the sky and noticed the same lights in the same flight pattern; which was odd. at that point the lights should of been farther away. i watched the lights to see where they were going and proceeded to witness strange maneuvers. it would fly straight, stop and hover for a few beats rise at an angle which would show it's belly (which was full of flashing). then it would fly up turn and take off only to return and repeat the same maneuver. i got the guy with the soccer ball to look after some nudging ( he thought i was crazy) and he saw it too. he told me it was fake and took off. i have been going to that park for over 5 years and never saw him before or since. strange. after a few more minutes of watching, i decided to go across the street to the bigger park and see if this was some practical joke. that is when i noticed the police helicopters and cars circling the park. so i left. the disc flew away at the sign of the helicopter
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription: Tuesday night around 1230 am i was sitting in my living room when something caught my eye as being very bright and moving straight across my back yard about 300 feet in the air. it moved from one end of the property to other in a fairly quick manner but not incredible fast. what was strange was the red to orange to white trail the looked sort of like fire but was much more stable and the edges were sharper than a fire. i watched it pass sitting down and immediatly got up after i couldn't see it any more because of my angle in the house. by the time i got outside it was gone, which was even more odd because we are up on hill and can see for a long way. for that reason and the composition of the glowing trail it didn't add up as an airplane. and we see a lot of small airplanes fly around here and this wasn't anything like those. i thought about this for the last few days and went online to see if maybe someone else may have seen and posted and to my complete surprise i found a post here on mufon from someone with the exact same description on the same night and same time in sun prairi which is like 30 miles due west of us.
content.summary: Red, orand to white trail from something moving above tree line

content.detailedDescription:
Setting: night, mostly clear sky.

at around 9:15pm pst/pdt, inside my home, in a suburb of aliso viejo, ca, i was disturbed by the sounds of a helicopter outside in a "search" pattern.

after about five minutes of the helicopter noise, and also my wife becoming disturbed with the noise, i went outside to investigate.

note: normally a helicopter (police or otherwise) would seldom fly over the house, and would not remain in close pattern above my neighborhood.

after going outside, i identified at least two helicopters in an irregular "orbit" pattern at about 200-500ft agl at the south/east region of boundary oak and wood canyon, just north/east of soka university.

immediately adjacent, i observed a disc shaped ufo at the same location in a wobbling hover mode (pitching and rolling about 15-30deg) and with a slow (not more than 20-30 mph) north/west translation.

the object shape, flight pattern, lights, and sound, was clearly not consistent with conventional rotary wing aircraft or their flight patterns, and hence, i concluded it was an ���unidentified��� object.

the ufo disc shape was inferred by a clearly observed ring of discrete lights (between 8-15 lights, may have been circles or squares) that appeared to line the perimeter of the bottom of the object.  i was not able to see any other shape features.  i am uncertain on the color of the lights (may have been white/yellow/orange).

the helicopters (at least two were observed) were holding in a tight pattern to the south/east and to the north/west of the object, and appeared to be "investigating" the object.  the type and markings on the helicopters were not visible from my location. 
the helicopters kept a distance of a few hundred feet from the object.

the size of the object was estimated somewhere between 30 to 40 ft in diameter, and was at least the size of the adjacent helicopters.

the object did not make any noise that i could discern over the sound of the adjacent helicopters.

both my wife and i observed the object in a slow hover for at least a few minutes.  then, it moved slowly to the north/west and below the horizon of the homes in the suburb. we did not see the object or helicopters reappear to our location.

i then left the neighborhood in my car to try and find the object.  in the process, i came across a group of at least 4 neighbors together outside, at least one with a camera, that all observed the same object, and were visibly agitated.  i���m not sure if the person with the camera got a picture.

from a hilltop near soka university, i could see the helicopters in the distance to the north/west, now in the laguna beach area.  from that distance, i could not discern the object.  a few minutes later, there appeared to be additional helicopters that joined the "search", probably 3-5 helicopters in total.

by 10:30pm, and after looking from two other hill/mountain top locations, the number of aircraft lights decreased to at least 1 (probably a helicopter).  i then ended my searching at this point.
content.summary: Disc in hover above suburb observed by helicopters and witnesses

content.detailedDescription:
My son and i were eastbound on i-80 on saturday 30 aug 2008 at 2242 hours.  while approximately 1/2 mile west of minooka road there appeared on the south side of i-80 and likely over the area of minooka rd., a sphere of light, traveling west at not a high rate of speed.  the altitude was perhaps as high as 2000 feet.  as it closed on us i kept looking at the object expecting to see other lights on it.  we were traveling at about 70mph and due to the amount of traffic i could not pull off to view the ufo due to safety concerns.  i instructed my son to keep it in his view until such time as i could pull off.

after just about 2 minutes in view, my son stated that the light simply went out.  it did not appear to fly away but instead simply blinked out or disappeared. at this point the object was behind us and to the right, out of my view but within my sons field of view.

the object appeared as a ball of yellowish light, not very bright but incandescent in its brightness or the color of flame.  i did not, nor at my direction, did my son view any other lights on the object as would appear on any conventional aircraft.
content.summary: Illuminated sphere of yellow light

content.detailedDescription:
At 05:00 hours i went outside to the backyard with my dog as usual. and as usual i was looking at the stars, trying to think about the different constellations and then i noticed a star out of place. i thought it strange and started to question myself that i had not noticed the star before.

all of a sudden the star started blimking in diferent colors, mostly white, red and flashes of blue. then it made a semicircle motion, appeared to move down, then it turned bright white and moved up extremely fast and disappeared.

even though i have seen many other "stars" and "thing" in the sky since i was a child, i still feel awed when i see it happen again. i felt pretty calm, my dog was also calm, the sky was pretty clear even though we are expecting a storm, we have a new moon in the sky so there was hardly any interference. at that time in the morning i was observing cassiopeia and my eye wandered to the left of it about 2 degrees and that is when i saw the "star". had it remained still i would not have given it any more thought. this is the first time i have seen one fly up though.

i do live close to an civilian airport that is connected to a military airport. watching airplanes and helicopters is nothing new to me (retired military)and the civilian flights do not start arriving until 05:40 hours and military flights don't start till 07:40 hours. in order to be at the same place as this "star" they would be approaching from the east, and normally when they do this they are about 200 to 300 feet up from my house. this particular object seemed to be about 1000 or more feet up.
content.summary: Flashing light that circled then went straight up.

content.detailedDescription:
When i was approximately 6 or 7 years of age i and my father who is now deceased witnessed the following sighting.
we lived on a farm between pickerington and baltimore near the community of harley on hwy 256. at approximately 8:00pm sometime during the summer months i and my father were standing on the front porch. at a distance of what i would guess was 5 to 7 miles south of us we saw a very large blimp like object. the object was at least 6 times the size of a regular blimp. i estimate the altitude to be 1000 to 1500 feet. the blimp like object was covered with hundreds of lights, white, red, green, blue and orange. the object was traveling east to west on a line that would take the object just south of columbus ohio. i asked my father what is it and he replied son it���s not a blimp, at that moment one of the lights on the bottom of the object grew brighter in color and then dropped strait down falling at a high rate of speed. it fell to approximately 200 feet then came strait toward our house at a high rate of speed steadily dropping in altitude until it was just above the corn field across the street then right before impacting our house it made a sharp left hand turn to the west. as it turned i felt the heat and saw the flame on the rear of the object. it looked as if it was a small disc or flat missile shape 10 feet long and 5 to 6 feet wide and about 3 to 4 feet thick. as it turned to the west it accelerated at an extremely fast rate and climbed out of site within seconds. as we turned back to the larger blimp like object it was now moving west and out of our sight. the sighting lasted approximately 20 to 30 minutes. the next morning we went to the corn field just next to the house where the small object had turned just before impacting our house. we observed that the corn was burned on the top of the plants in a strait path heading off to the west for 100 to 200 feet. the burn pattern was about 4 feet wide.  my father called someone ���i don���t know who��� to report the incident. that afternoon 2 men dressed in suits and identified themselves as federal agents came to our house and talked to me and my father about what we had observed. after taking our statements they told us what we saw was a weather balloon, because the weather service had launched them from the airport in columbus that afternoon. funny thing is my father worked at the columbus airport and he did not believe the agents and stated so after they had left. he told me son what we saw was no weather balloon or blimp.
content.summary: Large blimp like object - and - small disc or flat missile shape

content.detailedDescription:
Attending a cub scout event with my son at arbor lake in westminster, colorado.  the weather was clear blue and i noticed a stationary object that i could not identify with the naked eye. 

so i borrowed a pair of binoculars and observed what appeared to be
a self illuminated amber disc that seemed to sometimes become two objects, although it may have been an optical illusion(when it sepearated). 

at first, i thought it might be a balloon of some sort but it was absolutely stationary for at least 15 minutes. 

altitude was difficult to determine, but i would guess 10k to 20k feet above the ground. about 1/3 the size of a thumb-tack. no noise. remained stationary for about 15 minutes and then starting moving at an almost negligable speed from it's position nw of me towards the se.  when it reached a point of being almost directly overhead
it vanished. i couldn't say it went up, it just disappeared. 

during and after the event was excited and curious as to its nature.
i was also happy that my son was able to view something so extraordinary and that we could share the experience.

many witnesses, but not much reaction from the crowd? that struck me as curious. they seemed to just want to forget about it.
content.summary: Stationary disc, illuminated amber, seemed to seperate in two several times.
